				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Charm Kiting at 38 - what am I doing wrong?<a name="22465"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 19 04 11:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi Guys,
<br />

<br />
I've been fear kiting up until this level and for a change thought I would try charm kiting.
<br />

<br />
I am having lots of problems though. My charm doesn't stick more than 10 seconds or so. I have 187 CHA, should it be higher? By the time I have charmed the pet and set it on the target and started to chant my target, charm has broken and I have 2 very angry mobs after me. I can usually recharm but by that time, my target is so angry at me, the pet can't get aggro. I try to snare the target so my pet can catch up to it and so I can pet kite it to kill it but by the time I get that done, charm has broken again. Lather, rinse, repeat.
<br />

<br />
As you can see I am having all sorts of problems. What am I doing wrong? <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" /></span></td>
