			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Charm Kiting at 38 - what am I doing wrong?<a name="22616"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 19 04 9:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I wouldn't hold off learning to charm kite with the low lvl charm. Learning to use this song effectively is a must! This song is great for teaching bards how to really manipulate our class. 
<br />

<br />
First go try it on green mobs so you dont have to worry about running from 2 angry mobs, seriously practice on some non caster bandits in WK.
<br />

<br />
Next when you charm it's gonna look like this:
<br />
Selo
<br />
target pet start Charm (pet mob)
<br />
target attack mob before charm lands
<br />
charm lands, hit pet attack hotkey
<br />
selo (one pulse)
<br />
selo (one pulse)
<br />
target pet start Charm (pet mob)
<br />
target attack mob before charm lands
<br />
charm lands, hit pet attack hotkey
<br />
selo (one pulse)
<br />
selo (one pulse)
<br />

<br />
then when your pet is low on health chant him down.
<br />

<br />
Dont bother chanting the mob your attacking because when you recharm your pet all agro he built up before is wiped clean. Where as all your DOT dmg is still agroing mob.
<br />

<br />
The key is to make sure your switching targets while you are casting charm. Your spell target should always be ahead of your actual twist.
<br />

<br />
Hope you read this, hope it helps.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
