			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Charm Kiting at 38 - what am I doing wrong?<a name="22625"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 19 04 11:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi Charmer!
<br />

<br />
1st off, read Kalpton post again, because its right on target. Wind instrument is important for charming, as well as mezzing, and, alas, also useful for breaking charm when pet about to die and doting both ex-pet and mob for experience.
<br />

<br />
There is a nice LDoN BB Augment for 220 points (might take a little while to get there at your level, maybe 10 adventures depending on points at lvl 38, but experience is ok. At least it's a break from soloing, and allows you to try your group skills. And trust me, people will beg you for LDoN groups minutes after you put LFG up). Better yet, there is a nice necklace at EF camp for another 200+ points, Neclace of Forgotten Magic or something like that, that you can use to place the augment on, so you always get your wind instrument bonus while charming, mezzing, without having to swap weapons. I cannot recall the level requirement for Necklace (if any).
<br />

<br />
At your level, I would get a good drum, mem the 2 chants and go to South Karana and charm Gnolls (camp now mostly empty as most old world zones). 18 sec charm is so short, your best bet is pulling 6 or so Gnolls, get them in a tight circle (having drum on so you can selo and keep a confortable distance - since you got the LDoN BB Wind Instrument Mod Augment <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />), charm one, send pet to another, circle around the 2 mobs fighting, other Gnolls should agro pet, they will be all beating on pet, so when pet about to die, sing invisibility, and chant ex-pet down. Wash, winse reapeat with rest of Gnolls. Do not chant dots on mob pet is at, or dot agro will make that mob chase you forever, so when you recharm pet when charm breaks, that mob won't be on pet, but on you. You can keep targeting clean using F1 (targets you and your pet back and forth as you hit it). You can also use Toggle key to send pet against the same mob after every recharm if so you wish.
<br />

<br />
But of course, by the time you get the BB Wind Instrument Augment, you will be 39 already... Longer charm, less targetting work... easier charming. Just have the wind instrument you are using ready to be swapped by a drum and viceversa, accordingly.
<br />

<br />
Ah, and for practicing wind instrument as someone says above. You can use it at Bazzar, but if you are not a trader fan (I am too lazy myself. My bank account is at -50K atm with Chantie main, ROFL!! Necro got Spell: Blood of Thule <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> ), you can also go down to a hometown (I used Felwithe as Half-Elf Bard), throw yourself into a pond, find a little corner you can hit autorun and get stucked there and while singing EB and practicing Wind Instrument Skill, you are also practicing Swimming Skill! Phinny, watch it, here I come! (killed him today again, I was main tank, LOL. Just 3 of us - already had epic peice, dropped again. Mage's didn't, poor thing).
<br />

<br />
Be safe out there, but over anything be brave! You are a bard!
<br />

<br />
Nilufer</span></td>
