				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm only level 33 and I must have had better luck-I never have any problem swarming with charm, and I've been doing it since level 28.  18 seconds may not seem like much to most of you, but it's plenty of time for 8 ulthorks to beat my newfound friend/pet down to 20%.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I think more then anything it's just a matter of understanding the toggle switch key you've set up.  Once my charm hits I'm golden as long as I can quickly pick an attack target and switch back to my pet.  I've also begun to realize this toggle's effectiveness in grouping when I'm called on to mez for crowd control...wow, I wish I had known about this when I played an enchanter-I would have made it to 65 and Orehn probably never would have came about then.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
My newbie bard advice is to keep trying.  The best part about playing a bard is that under normal circumstances (read, outdoor zone) you can easily run away from any trouble you find yourself in.  Don't trust that charm spell to last for it's duration?  No problem, give it a shot and if it fails simply selo yourself to safety.
<br />

<br />
Then again, maybe I'm just different.  I wouldn't worry much about charm soloing just yet anyway-with LDoN I'm sure you'll soon find as I have that grouping is much more fun then running in circles or figure eights. =)</span></td>
