				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Charm Kiting at 38 - what am I doing wrong?<a name="22639"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 20 04 3:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The first song is great.  When you get 39 charm, you'll be mad that you run out of mana so fast and that it takes SO long to regen it (until you get some FT items)
<br />

<br />
So I recommend you use 27 charm as long as it still sticks on the mobs you are charming.
<br />

<br />
Another thing is to pick on mobs that have less magic resist.  You can also cast Fufil's on them first, if you like, to lower their magic resistance.  I've found (and other players dispute this) that charm will most often break on the first tick after the charm, and much less likely after that... so if you can get the charm to last for the first couple of ticks, you are more likely to have it last for the duration  (more important for the 39 song, of course).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
